8. MAIN API REQUIREMENTS
==================================================
Implement these REST endpoints.

A. Search eligible listings
GET /api/listings/search

Query params:
- renterId optional
- city optional
- startDate required
- endDate required
- minDailyRate optional
- maxDailyRate optional
- transmissionType optional
- fuelType optional
- minSeatCount optional
- sortBy optional (dailyRate, year)
- sortDirection optional (asc, desc)
- page optional
- size optional

Behavior:
1. load listing candidates from CarListing table
2. filter by search criteria
3. if renterId is present:
   - fetch renter profile
   - evaluate owner rules against renter
4. check date availability through Car Service
5. exclude listings that are not available or not eligible
6. return paginated eligible cars

B. Get listing by carId
GET /api/listings/{carId}

C. Sync one car from Car Service into Listing projection
POST /api/listings/sync/{carId}

D. Sync all active cars from Car Service
POST /api/listings/sync

E. Preview eligibility for one car and renter
GET /api/listings/{carId}/eligibility?renterId=...&startDate=...&endDate=...

Response should include:
- carId
- renterId
- eligibilityStatus
- available
- matchedRules
- failedRules
- warnings

==================================================
9. BUSINESS RULES
==================================================
Implement and document these rules:

1. startDate must be before endDate
2. rental period must be at least 1 day
3. only active listings should appear in search
4. only cars with non-expired tech inspection should appear
5. only cars with non-expired insurance should appear
6. if Car Service says car is unavailable for date range, do not show it
7. if renterId is provided, only show cars whose mandatory rules are satisfied
8. non-mandatory rules may be included as informational notes
9. CITY_ONLY rule should compare requested city / pickup city if provided, otherwise renter home city if available
10. Listing Service is only pre-filtering; Rental Service will still re-validate during booking

